{
  "texts": [
    "Nonetheless, there is a considerable divergence across the results reported by different papers even on the same dataset, as they employed various evaluation criteria and learning schemas.",
    "Despite the existence of some benchmarks for anomaly detection algorithms [11]- [16], they struggle to provide practical guidance for industrial domain experts to apply and develop deep learning methods as they pay more attention to statistical methods.",
    "In general, applying TSAD algorithms to practical systems faces these main obstacles: (I) Training specific model for each time series and deploying an exclusive model for each time series results in unaffordable maintenance costs.",
    "(II) New systems are more likely to encounter issues when first launched or upgraded, which makes anomaly detection even more essential despite their almost non-existent volume of historical data.",
    "(III) Existing metrics hold one-sided assumptions for evaluating how well the algorithms perform, which cannot offer an effective reference for industrial practice."
  ]
}